New Records: Glenn Maxwell scored the fastest century in World Cups, breaking Aiden Markram's record by 9 balls
Bas de Leede delivered the most expensive over in men's ODI history
Key Match Events: Australia posted 399/8, their highest score in the World Cup so far
Netherlands were bowled out for 90, their lowest score in the World Cup so far
David Warner scored his 22nd ODI hundred and 6th World Cup century
Glenn Maxwell scored his 3rd overall century and 2nd World Cup century, and his fastest century in World Cups
Bas de Leede's final over cost 43 runs, with 28 of them coming from Glenn Maxwell
Post-Match Reflections: Scott Edwards, the Netherlands captain, said that the defeat will not define his team
Glenn Maxwell celebrated his century with a baby-rocking celebration, a nod to his wife and first child, Logan, who was born last month
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the largest margin of victory in men's ODI World Cup history
Adam Zampa secured his third successive four-for
Mitchell Starc came and went for a golden duck, leaving Pat Cummins to close out the innings with just his second boundary
